Here is the full security report based on what was found in your actual codebase.

---

## REQUIREMENT 1 — Advanced RLS SQL

### What the audit found
40 of 41 tables have RLS enabled. Your `support_tickets` table has **no CREATE TABLE, no RLS, no policies** — only ALTER statements on a table that may not exist in prod yet. Everything else is solid.

### Exact SQL to apply

**support_tickets — create, enable RLS, add policies:**
```sql
-- Run this if the table doesn't exist yet in prod
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.support_tickets (
  id          UUID        PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id     UUID        NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  subject     TEXT        NOT NULL,
  message     TEXT        NOT NULL,
  type        TEXT        NOT NULL DEFAULT 'general' CHECK (type IN ('general', 'bug')),
  status      TEXT        NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open'    CHECK (status IN ('open', 'closed')),
  admin_reply TEXT,
  replied_at  TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);

ALTER TABLE public.support_tickets ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Users can only see their own tickets
CREATE POLICY "tickets_select_own"
  ON public.support_tickets FOR SELECT
  USING (user_id = auth.uid());

-- Users can only create tickets for themselves
CREATE POLICY "tickets_insert_own"
  ON public.support_tickets FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (user_id = auth.uid());

-- Users cannot update tickets — only admins do (via service role / SECURITY DEFINER fn)
-- No UPDATE policy for anon/authenticated roles intentionally
```

**feedback — tighten the overly-broad SELECT policy:**
```sql
-- Current policy lets ANY authenticated user read ALL feedback rows — wrong
DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "feedback_select" ON public.feedback;

CREATE POLICY "feedback_select_own"
  ON public.feedback FOR SELECT
  USING (user_id = auth.uid());
```

**Workspace-shared tables (invoices / contracts) — the correct junction pattern:**

Your current RLS gates invoices and contracts on `user_id = auth.uid()`. If you later allow workspace members to collaborate on documents, use this pattern — **do not apply until workspace sharing is a real feature**:

```sql
-- Junction table (create once)
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.workspace_members (
  workspace_id  UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES public.workspaces(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id       UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id)        ON DELETE CASCADE,
  role          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'member' CHECK (role IN ('owner', 'admin', 'member')),
  joined_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  PRIMARY KEY (workspace_id, user_id)
);

ALTER TABLE public.workspace_members ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Members can see other members in their own workspaces
CREATE POLICY "wm_select"
  ON public.workspace_members FOR SELECT
  USING (
    user_id = auth.uid()
    OR workspace_id IN (
      SELECT workspace_id FROM public.workspace_members WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
    )
  );

-- Only owners/admins can add members
CREATE POLICY "wm_insert"
  ON public.workspace_members FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (
    workspace_id IN (
      SELECT workspace_id FROM public.workspace_members
      WHERE user_id = auth.uid() AND role IN ('owner', 'admin')
    )
  );

-- Only owners/admins can remove members; members cannot escalate their own role
CREATE POLICY "wm_delete"
  ON public.workspace_members FOR DELETE
  USING (
    workspace_id IN (
      SELECT workspace_id FROM public.workspace_members
      WHERE user_id = auth.uid() AND role IN ('owner', 'admin')
    )
  );

-- ── When workspace sharing is live, replace invoices policy with this ──
DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "invoices_select_own" ON public.invoices;

CREATE POLICY "invoices_select_workspace"
  ON public.invoices FOR SELECT
  USING (
    user_id = auth.uid()   -- owner always sees their own
    OR workspace_id IN (   -- or any active member of the same workspace
      SELECT workspace_id FROM public.workspace_members
      WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
    )
  );

-- INSERT: user must be a member of the workspace they are writing into
CREATE POLICY "invoices_insert_workspace"
  ON public.invoices FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (
    user_id = auth.uid()
    AND (
      workspace_id IS NULL  -- personal invoice, no workspace
      OR workspace_id IN (
        SELECT workspace_id FROM public.workspace_members
        WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
      )
    )
  );

-- UPDATE/DELETE: only the original owner
CREATE POLICY "invoices_update_own"
  ON public.invoices FOR UPDATE
  USING (user_id = auth.uid())
  WITH CHECK (user_id = auth.uid());

CREATE POLICY "invoices_delete_own"
  ON public.invoices FOR DELETE
  USING (user_id = auth.uid());

-- Apply the same pattern to contracts
```

