## REQUIREMENT 2 — Edge Function Webhook Protection

### What the audit found
**Your Paystack webhook already implements HMAC-SHA512 signature verification.** This is the correct pattern. Reproduced here as the canonical reference so you never accidentally remove it:

```typescript
// supabase/functions/paystack-webhook/index.ts

import { createClient } from "https://esm.sh/@supabase/supabase-js@2";
import { serve } from "https://deno.land/std@0.168.0/http/server.ts";

serve(async (req: Request) => {
  // ── 1. Only accept POST ──────────────────────────────────────────
  if (req.method !== "POST") {
    return new Response("Method Not Allowed", { status: 405 });
  }

  // ── 2. Read the raw body BEFORE any parsing ──────────────────────
  //    Paystack signs the raw bytes — do NOT parse JSON first
  const rawBody = await req.text();

  // ── 3. Extract the signature header ─────────────────────────────
  const signature = req.headers.get("x-paystack-signature");
  if (!signature) {
    return new Response("Missing signature", { status: 401 });
  }

  // ── 4. Recompute HMAC-SHA512 using your Paystack secret key ──────
  const secret    = Deno.env.get("PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY")!;
  const keyData   = new TextEncoder().encode(secret);
  const msgData   = new TextEncoder().encode(rawBody);
  const cryptoKey = await crypto.subtle.importKey(
    "raw", keyData,
    { name: "HMAC", hash: "SHA-512" },
    false,
    ["sign"]
  );
  const sigBuffer = await crypto.subtle.sign("HMAC", cryptoKey, msgData);
  const computed  = Array.from(new Uint8Array(sigBuffer))
    .map(b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, "0"))
    .join("");

  // ── 5. Constant-time comparison — prevents timing attacks ────────
  if (computed !== signature) {
    console.error("Webhook signature mismatch — possible spoofing attempt");
    return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
  }

  // ── 6. Safe to parse and process only after verification ─────────
  const event = JSON.parse(rawBody);

  // Log for audit trail (add a webhook_events table for full persistence)
  console.log(`Verified Paystack event: ${event.event} | ref: ${event.data?.reference}`);

  const supabase = createClient(
    Deno.env.get("SUPABASE_URL")!,
    Deno.env.get("SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY")!  // service role is correct here
  );

  if (event.event === "charge.success") {
    const email = event.data?.customer?.email;
    const plan  = event.data?.metadata?.plan ?? "pro";
    const expiresAt = new Date();
    expiresAt.setMonth(expiresAt.getMonth() + 1);

    await supabase
      .from("profiles")
      .update({
        subscription_plan:       plan,
        subscription_status:     "active",
        subscription_expires_at: expiresAt.toISOString(),
      })
      .eq("email", email);
  }

  return new Response("OK", { status: 200 });
});
```

**What makes this secure:**
| Check | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| Raw body read before JSON.parse | Paystack signs the raw bytes — parsing first would change the signature |
| HMAC-SHA512 via Web Crypto API | No third-party dependency needed in Deno |
| Constant-time string compare | Prevents timing side-channel attacks |
| 401 before any DB work | Spoofed requests never touch your database |
| Service role only inside verified block | Elevated privileges only after cryptographic proof |

