## REQUIREMENT 3 — Frontend Security Checklist

### .env key management — rules you must never break

```
# ✅ SAFE — public keys, designed to be exposed
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=...
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=...
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=...
VITE_PAYSTACK_PUBLIC_KEY=...

# ❌ THESE MUST NEVER HAVE THE VITE_ PREFIX
# If they do, Vite bundles them into the JS output and they are
# visible to anyone who opens DevTools or downloads your app

SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=...     # never VITE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=...           # never VITE_PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY
OPENAI_API_KEY=...                # never VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY
RESEND_API_KEY=...                # never VITE_RESEND_API_KEY
```

**The audit confirmed: none of your secret keys are VITE_ prefixed. Keep it that way.**

The single pattern to grep for before every deploy:
```bash
grep -r "VITE_.*SECRET\|VITE_.*SERVICE_ROLE\|VITE_.*OPENAI\|VITE_.*RESEND" src/
# Should return nothing. If it returns anything, stop and fix it.
```

### XSS — patterns to avoid when rendering user-generated content

**The audit confirmed: you have zero unsafe HTML rendering.** All user content (invoice notes, client addresses, contract content, profile bios) goes through React JSX text nodes which auto-escape everything. Keep these rules:

```tsx
// ✅ SAFE — React escapes all HTML entities automatically
<p>{invoice.notes}</p>
<p>{invoice.client_address}</p>
<p>{contract.content}</p>

// ❌ NEVER DO THIS with user content
<p dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: invoice.notes }} />
<p dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: contract.content }} />

// ❌ NEVER DO THIS
element.innerHTML = userInput;
document.write(userInput);

// ❌ NEVER DO THIS
eval(userInput);
new Function(userInput)();
```

**The one place you DO use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`** is `src/components/ui/chart.tsx` for CSS theme injection — that is safe because the values come from hardcoded config objects, not user input. Do not change it.

**If you ever add a rich-text / markdown editor** (e.g., for contract content), sanitize before render:
```tsx
// Install: npm install dompurify @types/dompurify
import DOMPurify from "dompurify";

// ✅ Safe rich-text render
<div dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{
  __html: DOMPurify.sanitize(contract.content, {
    ALLOWED_TAGS: ["p", "b", "i", "ul", "ol", "li", "br", "strong", "em"],
    ALLOWED_ATTR: []  // no href, no onclick, no style
  })
}} />
```

